  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Water for Bandhavgarh&apos;s Tigers - Reducing Conflict</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Climate Change has led to severe drought becoming the norm in Bandhavgarh as annual monsoon rainfall reduces. The impact is felt by all as herbivores enter villages to drink &amp; raid crops; predators follow taking livestock. Villagers can&apos;t afford to lose crops &amp; livestock so they try fair or foul means to end the conflict risking tigers&apos; lives. Our project will provide solar-powered borehole pumps to provide year-round water for tigers &amp; their prey thus reducing human-animal conflict &amp; impact</narrative>
  </description>
